>foster an intelligent approach to performance management whereby:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 56.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Indicators are used to inform our learning and understanding of an issue, as opposed to being a single measure of success or failure</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 56.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Numerical measures are not viewed in isolation of the wid</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">er objectives of my plan</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 56.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Alternative sources of assurance are obtained through diagnostic information, dip testing and my interactions with residents, victims, organisations and stakeholders</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 56.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The principles of quality and victim-focussed services remain cen</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">tral.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">1.1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The terminology contained within my plan is important as it reflects my desire to move away from a primarily target-driven culture in favour of a more balanced approach that considers the wider objectives and the behaviours they drive. I have not, for exam</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ple used the term ‘target’ in my Police and Crime Plan, but instead made reference to ‘indicators’ and ‘ambitions’.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">1.1.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I do not believe that the nine Police and Crime measures alone can tell us whether we are achieving the aspirations of the plan, but I do</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> recognise their importance in helping us to understand and communicate progress against a complex area of business to a wide variety of audiences. I also feel that there is a public and organisational desire for clear tangible outcomes against my overall </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ambition which I have aimed to balance proportionately within my Police and Crime Plan.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">1.2. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> What impact do you think these targets have on police recording crime practices?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">1.2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Of the nine ambitions set as part of my Police and Crime Plan, four r</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ely upon police recorded crime data.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> I have engaged with officers and staff at a various levels of the organisation to develop an understanding of the impact of my priorities and the small number of numerical indicators that support them.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> This will culmi</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">nate in a meeting with performance and priority leads in January ahead of the annual refresh of my Police and Crime Plan.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">1.2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">In addition to this oversight, the Constabulary has reviewed attitudes, perceptions and behaviours with regard to performance cultu</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">re through its performance review process as part of a programme of work to drive improvements in crime recording standards.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> Active oversight of this work has helped to inform my view.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">1.2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I have concluded that there is evidence to suggest that a historic or</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ganisational target-driven culture has, at times, led to pressure on staff to behave in a way that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">puts performance ahead of the victim when recording crime.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> This was supported by a recent internal poll of officers and staff in Avon and Somerset.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">1.2.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I feel </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">confident, however, that the organisation has undergone a significant cultural shift over recent years, which has resulted in a more analytical and less target-driven approach to driving performance improvement. While this is clearly evident at senior leve</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ls within the organisation, I share a desire to ensure that this is effectively communicated and fully recognised at all levels within the organisation.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">1.2.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I believe that the safeguards to ensuring an accurate, ethical and reliable approach to crime recordin</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">g lie in the organisation’s approach to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">performance culture</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> more generally as opposed to the concept of measurable aspirations as part of the Police and Crime Plan.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> I do however recognise that I have a role to play in shaping this culture both through the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> plan and in my interactions with officers and staff, and will continue to review my approach in light of new and emerging findings.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">1.2.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">There are, however, a number of areas where my </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">strategic priorities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> have had a direct impact upon crime recording practice</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> In 2013, for example, the Constabulary introduced a flag for commercial burglary which enabled the organisation to improve analysis and interventions in response to my burglary reduction priority.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> Similarly, a focus on improving crime recording standa</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">rds with regard to domestic violence resulted in earlier and more accurate identification of domestic violence victims.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> While this has not been driven by an increase in victim reporting it is clearly a positive outcome in enabling greater identification, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">support and safeguarding amongst victims of these crimes.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How do you assure yourself that the recorded crime figures for your area are correct?</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2.1.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I actively seek assurance with regard to the accuracy of crime data through a variety of mechanisms and recognise that our intelligence, analysis, operational effectiveness and service provision are all dependent upon the information we record and process.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2.1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">There has been a dedicated programme of work in Avon and Somerset to improve crime recording standards prompted by HMIC Crime and Incident Recording Inspections and key findings from HMIC’s work in Kent in February 2013. This led to a Gold and Silver G</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">roup being established and I am represented on both.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> As part of this process, I maintain ongoing oversight of crime recording compliance and progress against a dedicated improvement plan.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2.1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I also directly oversee issues relating to crime recording and dat</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">a integrity through my regular 1:1 meetings with respective Chief Officer Portfolio holders for crime recording and performance. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2.1.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">While these internal oversight arrangements provide some level of assurance, I also place great value on external and indepen</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">dent sources of assurance, including the HMIC inspection which offers broader comparisons against other police forces nationally.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2.2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">To what extent can you trust the crime statistics for your area? </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2.2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">My trust in the recorded crime statistics for Avon and Som</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">erset is borne out of a realistic understanding of the limitations of this data and what the crime statistics represent.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> I understand, for example, that they can only ever be a reflection of what is reported to or pro-actively identified by the police, an</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">d for a variety of reasons, would not rely on police recorded crime statistics to give an indication of overall levels or trends in crime.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">2.2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">In my view, the important question is whether we and our partner organisations can trust the recorded crime data t</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">o accurately identify the nature of victimisation, risk and vulnerability.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> This is critical to ensuring appropriate and effective victim focussed service responses and safeguarding our most vulnerable people from harm.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> While I understand that volume crim</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">e data is always likely to contain some margin of error, I believe that further work can still be done to mitigate these risks. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">2.2.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I recognise that Avon and Somerset has been consistently identified as having one of the lowest levels of compliance nationall</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">y across areas such as incident to crime conversion - while also having one of the highest rates of no crime decisions.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> These </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">findings are a source of shared concern, however, I am now confident that the Constabulary is working hard to drive sustained imp</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">rovements in the accuracy of the data they record and retain.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">2.2.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I have been particularly encouraged by the Constabulary’s approach in seeking to understand the drivers of poor quality recording and tailor their solutions accordingly – be they training, system and process improvement, supervision and leadership, culture</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> or capacity.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> Recent developments have included:- </span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 56.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Additional auditing and review of no-crime decisions</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 56.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Corporate communication messages</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 56.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">New processes and mandatory fields on crime recording systems to ensure essential information is completed</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 56.32pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Revised rol</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">es and structures within the organisation to improve efficiency and effectiveness and remove the risk of competing priorities</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">2.2.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">In October 2013, the force volunteered to be a pilot area for HMIC’s upcoming Crime Recording Inspection.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> This offered valuable </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">learning and opportunities to independently identify important areas for improvement.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 42.55pt; text-indent:-42.55pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">2.2.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Through my oversight of internal quality audits and activity of the Crime Recording Gold Group, I feel confident that crime recording standards in Avon and Somerset ar</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">e improving and improving at a considerable pace.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> I will continue to support the Constabulary in instilling an intelligent, ethical, open and transparent performance culture while continuing to drive improvements in crime recording standards and public se</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">rvice standards more generally.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Should you wish any further information or any clarification of any of the enclosed please feel free to contact us.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">January 2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>